#week-title("Two", "The Complete Account of the Three-Year Work")

=== Core Teaching

The Great Work Gathering requires that each student present a complete account
of their three-year Work. This is not a summary of the curriculum — it is an
account of what was actually done, what was actually observed, and where each
preparation currently stands.

The complete account covers:

*Year One — The Plant Stone:*
- Source plant (Melissa or alternative) and date of beginning
- Maceration: menstruum used, duration, colour at various stages
- Calcination: colour progression achieved, weight records, any vitrification
  errors and how they were addressed
- Distillation: hydrosol produced, oil fraction if separated
- Cohobation: number of cycles completed, diagnostic test results
- Current state: tincture, cohobated elixir, sealed digestion, or stone

*Year Two — Water Work and Long Circulation:*
- Archaeus of Water preparation: whether the Gur formed, what stage reached
- Border mineral work (Months 7 and 10): what was prepared and observed
- Long circulation: what preparation was sealed, when, and its current state
  after over a year of uninterrupted circulation

*Year Three — Mineral Work:*
- Vinegar of Antimony: production, sensory analysis, current storage
- Via Humida mineral preparation: mineral chosen, number of cycles completed,
  current colour stage
- Any additional mineral work undertaken (Butyrum, additional antimony
  preparations, iron or copper work)
- Current state of all active preparations

This account is assembled from the laboratory journal and Materia Medica
notebook — not from memory. The complete account is also the primary document
the student leaves with: a precise record of everything the Work has produced
across three years.

=== Topics This Week

- Assembling the complete account from laboratory journal and Materia Medica
- What to include: what was done, what was observed, current state of each preparation
- The Materia Medica as the complete account's companion document
- Reviewing for completeness before the Month 12 gathering

